  "prompt": "What does it mean when you can't sleep on your stomach?",
  "response": "When someone can't sleep on their stomach, it could be due to several reasons:\n\n1. Physical discomfort or pain\n- Back or neck strain\n- Pregnancy\n- Recent surgery\n- Spinal issues\n- Herniated disc\n\n2. Medical conditions\n- Acid reflux\n- Breathing difficulties\n- Shoulder or hip problems\n- Chronic pain conditions\n\n3. Physical characteristics\n- Large breasts\n- Being overweight\n- Muscle tension\n- Pregnancy (especially in later stages)\n\n4. Potential risks of stomach sleeping\n- Increased pressure on spine\n- Neck strain\n- Potential breathing restrictions\n- Potential nerve compression\n\n5. Recommended alternatives\n- Side sleeping\n- Back sleeping\n- Using supportive pillows\n- Changing sleep position gradually\n\nIf stomach sleeping consistently causes discomfort or pain, it's advisable to:\n- Consult a healthcare professional\n- Consider changing sleep positions\n- Use supportive mattresses and pillows\n- Do stretching exercises\n- Address underlying health issues\n\nThe specific reason varies by individual, so professional medical advice can help determine the exact cause.",
